# multiprocessing.pool.Pool.apply.__name__ == 'apply' (len=5)
# multiprocessing.pool.Pool.apply_async.__name__ == 'apply_async' (len=11)
#
# apply(func, args, kwds) executes func in a worker process and blocks until
# the result is ready. apply_async is the non-blocking variant that returns
# an AsyncResult. NAME LENGTHS: apply=5 < apply_async=11 (adds '_async'=6).
# New to extra176.
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------

